        "compendiumSource": null,
        "duplicateSource": null
      },
      "ownership": {
        "default": 0
      },
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Mustering its mass and energy, the tiny slime can infrequently grow to a dangerous size. As an action, its keeper can will its size to increase from Tiny to Medium once per day. This can be maintained for up to 10 minutes, using its keepers Concentration to maintain the effect. While enlarged, the slime is affected in the following ways:</span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-size: 13px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Its Armor Class increases to 18, however creatures have advantage on any attacks they make against it that deal lightning damage.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">If it should be hit with an attack while Medium size,&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">it immediately reverts back to its Tiny size.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">It acts on its keepers turn and its movement speed increases to 15 feet.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">As a bonus action, its keeper can will it to make two melee slam attacks against a creature within 5 feet of it. The bonus to hit with these is +4. On a hit, each slam deals 1d6 + 2 bludgeoning damage. Additionally, if the slime hits with its first attack, it has disadvantage on its second. If it misses on its first attack, it has advantage on its second.</span></li>\n</ul>",
          "chat": "",
          "unidentified": ""
        },
