    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p>Once this curious puddle of liquid is exposed to the magnetic field created by its control stone, the Slimestone, it animates and becomes receptive to direction—allowing it to assume bizarre geometric shapes, imitate the forms of humanoids or creatures, dance around, or ooze around its environment. The diminutive mass of sludge is also able to absorb moisture, dust motes, and other particles from the atmosphere and add these to its mass, enabling it to rapidly expand from about the size of a chicken to that of a barrel or crate, though it this form is unstable and the slime cannot maintain it for long.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong style=\"color:#191813;font-style:italic\">Rule Clarification, Slimestone.</strong><span style=\"color:#191813;font-style:italic\"> Full rules for the tiny slime can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.items.hSFBcCZ841BDekXF]{Slimestone}.</span></p>\n</blockquote>",
